'''Armando González Alba''' (born 20 April 2003), nicknamed "'''Hormiga'''" ({{lit|Ant|lk=on}})<ref>{{cite web|title={{space}}'Hormiga' González toma rumbo al Mundial|url=https://www.fifa.com/es/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/armando-gonzalez-chivas-seleccion-mexico-mundial-2026|website=FIFA.com|publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association|date=28 April 2026|access-date=6 June 2026|language=ES|trans-title='Hormiga' González heads to the World Cup}}</ref> is a Mexican professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[C.D. Guadalajara|Guadalajara]] and the [[Mexico national football team|Mexico national team]].

==Club career==
===Guadalajara===
====Tapatío====
González made his professional debut with [[C.D. Tapatío|Tapatío]] on 11 November 2020, coming on as a 89th-minute substitute against [[Pumas Tabasco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/11/19/mexico/liga-de-ascenso/tapatio/pumas-tabasco/3335654/ |title=Tapatío vs. Pumas Tabasco  4 - 2|publisher=Soccerway|date=11 November 2020|access-date=22 September 2024}}</ref>

====First team====
González made his first team, and [[Liga MX]] debut on 13 January 2024 coming on as a 85th-minute substitute in a 1–1 draw against [[Santos Laguna]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2024/01/14/mexico/primera-division/club-guadalajara/club-santos-laguna/4285256/ |title=Guadalajara vs. Santos Laguna  1 - 1|publisher=Soccerway|date=13 January 2024|access-date=22 September 2024}}</ref> He finished his debut season with just 3 appearances and no goals.

González scored his first goal for Guadalajara in a match against [[Club Tijuana|Tijuana]] on 12 July 2024, where Guadalajara would go on to lose 2–4.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/es/noticias/37972/Chivas-cae-ante-Xolos-en-la-frontera|title= Chivas cae ante Xolos en la frontera |publisher=Club Deportivo Guadalajara|date=13 July 2024|access-date=4 December 2025}}</ref>

On 26 July 2025, within the final minutes of the match, González would score a brace against [[Atlético San Luis]], helping ''Chivas'' guarantee a 4–3 home victory.<ref>https://www.heraldodeportes.com.mx/futbol/2025/7/26/hormiga-gonzalez-rescata-las-chivas-del-desastre-ante-san-luis-doblete-remontada-82167.html</ref>
On 25 October, González would score his first career hat-trick against [[Clásico Tapatío]] rivals [[Atlas F.C.|Atlas]] in a 4–1 win.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.record.com.mx/futbol/liga-mx/chivas/hormiga-gonzalez-se-convierte-en-el-7mo-jugador-de-chivas-en-marcar-un-hat |title= 'Hormiga' González se convierte en el 7mo jugador de Chivas en marcar un ‘Hat-trick’ en Clásico Tapatío |publisher=Récord|date=26 October 2025|access-date=4 December 2025}}</ref> He would go on to finish the season as the joint-top scorer with 12 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/en/noticias/40118/ARMANDO-GONZLEZ-ES-CAMPEN-DE-GOLEO-DEL-AP25 |title= ARMANDO GONZÁLEZ IS THE AP25 GOAL SCORING CHAMPION!!! |publisher=Club Deportivo Guadalajara|date=4 December 2025|access-date=25 November 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
González was called up to the senior [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] team by manager [[Javier Aguirre]] in November 2025 for friendly matches against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] and [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] set to be played on the 15 and 18 of November respectively. González made his debut appearance for Mexico on 18 November against Paraguay with his side losing the match 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|first=Ana Patricia|last=Spíndola Andrade|title=¡Noche soñada! Armando 'Hormiga' González se lleva mucho aprendizaje de su debut con Selección Mexicana|url=https://www.record.com.mx/futbol/futbol-nacional/seleccion-mexicana/noche-sonada-armando-hormiga-gonzalez-se-lleva-mucho|lang=es|website=Record.com.mx|date= 19 November 2025|access-date= 20 November 2025}}</ref> On 25 February 2026, González scored his debut goal with the national team against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]], the second in an eventual 4–0 win.<ref>https://www.marca.com/mx/futbol/seleccion-mx/2026/02/26/699fb631e2704ea9308b457c.html</ref>

==Personal life==
González is the son of former professional footballer [[Armando González (footballer, born 1968)|Armando González Bejarano]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chivasdecorazon.com.mx/en/noticias/37224/La-asombrosa-coincidencia-de-Mateo-Chvez-y-Armando-Gonzlez |title=The amazing coincidence of Mateo Chávez and Armando González|publisher=Club Deportivo Guadalajara|date=16 January 2024|access-date=22 September 2024}}</ref>

